metadata.name: Transparent Reflections #1/40
metadata.description:
Leaving Orcas Island on a cold, but sunny September day, I came across the opportunity to capture three scenes in one single frame. 

Behind me, reflected in the window's glass, a passenger was getting their morning stretch in. 

Just beyond the glass in front of me, there were empty seats in a seasonally-closed section of the ferry. 

Looking through that closed section were passengers on the other side of the ferry deck, framed in the windows.

Please enjoy, "Transparent Reflections".
